<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-01-13T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-01-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="889" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d889">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.672/7: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Special Mission at Lausanne</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-01-13T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 13,
                                        1923—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>83. The recommendations contained in your 194 of January 12 regarding the
                            discussion of a treaty of amity and commerce with the Turks have the
                            approval of the Department. You will receive more precise instructions.
                            In the meantime you are authorized to approach the Turkish delegation
                            informally in the matter and to report to the Department how your
                            advances are received.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
